# Publishing to jbdel/RadEval

This project has two repos:
- **hopprai/RadEval** (private, origin) -- full codebase with all metrics
- **jbdel/RadEval** (public) -- same codebase minus private metrics (e.g. HopprCheXbert)

## How to publish

All development happens on hopprai/RadEval. To release publicly:

```bash
# 1. Make sure all changes are committed and pushed to hopprai/RadEval
git add -A && git commit -m "..." && git push origin main

# 2. Dry-run first (see what will be stripped, no push)
python scripts/publish_public.py -m "v0.X.Y: description"

# 3. Push to public repo
python scripts/publish_public.py --push -m "v0.X.Y: description"
```

The script clones the **public** repo, replaces its working tree with the current
private repo state (minus private metrics/dirs/files), commits with the provided
message, and pushes normally. Private files never enter the public repo's history.

## PyPI workflow

Always build from the PUBLIC repo, never from hopprai/RadEval.

```bash
# After publish_public.py --push:
cd /tmp && git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/jbdel/RadEval.git radeval_pypi
cd radeval_pypi && python -m build --sdist
TWINE_USERNAME=__token__ TWINE_PASSWORD="<token from scripts/pypi>" twine upload dist/*
rm -rf /tmp/radeval_pypi
```

Bump `version` in `setup.py` before each PyPI upload.

## Adding a new private metric

Edit `PRIVATE_METRICS` in `scripts/publish_public.py`:

```python
PRIVATE_METRICS = [
    {
        "name": "hoppr_f1chexbert",              # human label
        "metric_dir": "RadEval/metrics/hoppr_f1chexbert",  # folder to delete
        "test_file": "tests/test_hopprf1chexbert.py",      # test to delete
        "flag": "do_f1hopprchexbert",               # constructor flag to strip
        "display_name": "HopprCheXbert",          # for logging
    },
    # Add new private metrics here with the same structure
]
```

The metric must also degrade gracefully when missing. Pattern:

1. `__init__.py` catches import errors: `try: from .mod import Cls; except: Cls = None`
2. `RadEval.py` wraps the init block in try/except and disables the flag on failure
3. Test file checks `if Cls is None: pytest.skip(...)`
